      • add

        public Monomial add(Monomial other)
        adds monomials that are combinable together into a single monomial. Note this add feature does not have functionality when the bases or degrees do not match as that would result in a polynomial answer.
        Parameters:
        other - is the Monomial being added.
        Returns:
        the Monomial that invoked it, now modified

      • subtract

        public Monomial subtract(Monomial other)
        subtracts a monomial only if it is compatible with the monomial resulting in a single monomial. Note this subtract feature does not have functionality when the bases or degree do not match as that would result in a polynomial answer.
        Parameters:
        other - is the Monomial being subtracted.
        Returns:
        the Monomial that invoked it, now modified

      • multiply

        public Monomial multiply(Monomial other)
        takes two monomials and multiplies them into a single monomial. Note this multiply feature is currently bound to monomials of the same base--_if we have time we will alow monomials to be multivariable.
        Parameters:
        other - is the monomial being multiplied with.
        Returns:
        a new Monomial which is the product of the invoking Monomial and other

      • divide

        public Monomial divide(Monomial other)
        takes two monomials and divides them into a single monomial. Note this divide feature does not work when the bases are of different variable.
        Parameters:
        other - is the monomial that we divide with.
        Returns:
        a new Monomial which is the quotient of the invoking Monomial and other
